Apple Core is a hard-fork of mattt/iMCP (https://github.com/mattt/iMCP),
licensed MIT, Copyright 2025 Mattt (https://mat.tt). iMCP's original
source files are preserved with their MIT copyright headers intact under
the one-way MIT-into-GPL compatibility described in
docs/planning/BUILD_PLAN.md §4. The full text of iMCP's license is kept
at THIRD_PARTY_LICENSES/iMCP.LICENSE.

Serving infrastructure (HTTP/SSE server, OAuth support, Cloudflare
tunnel management, LaunchAgent daemon registration) is ported from
Bridgeport (https://github.com/oliverames/bridgeport), a separate
personal project also authored by Oliver Ames. No third-party attribution
applies to this code.

Additional patterns and design research are drawn from a synthesis of
six other Apple-related MCP server projects, documented in full in
docs/planning/DONORS.md and docs/planning/SYNTHESIS.md. As of this
writing, none of that donor code has been lifted into this repository —
only the research and design decisions have been. When a future surface
implementation (Mail, Notes, Reminders extensions, etc.) actually lifts
code or a substantially-derived design from one of those projects, this
file and THIRD_PARTY_LICENSES/ must be updated at that time to include:

  - The donor project's name, URL, and license
  - A copy of its license text in THIRD_PARTY_LICENSES/<project>.LICENSE
  - A one-line note here naming which surface/pattern was lifted

See docs/planning/BUILD_PLAN.md §4.2 for the full attribution discipline
(per-file SPDX headers, commit-log conventions) to follow when that work
happens.
